    <section>
      <h2>What is SQL Query Lab and how does it work?</h2>
      <p>
        SQL Query Lab is a client-side SQL learning environment that uses <a href="https://sql.js.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer">sql.js</a> — SQLite compiled to WebAssembly — to execute SQL entirely in the browser. When you load the page, a pre-seeded SQLite database is initialized in memory. Your queries run against this in-browser database with sub-100ms latency, no network round-trip required. The tool supports three modes: <strong>Practice</strong> (structured challenges with validation), <strong>Sandbox</strong> (free-form SQL scratchpad with auto-save), and <strong>MS SQL</strong> (interactive T-SQL translation from SQLite syntax). The backend API (Node.js + Hono, deployed on DigitalOcean) handles real SQL Server connections when you use Live mode.
      </p>
    </section>

